# Source vs out

- Edit game logic in `source/scenes/**/*.scene.dry` and `source/qdisplays/*.qdisplay.dry` only (see `game-source-only.mdc`). Do not treat `source/lib/*.js` as authoritative for in-game behavior.
- **Reading `out/`** is fine (compiled `core.js`, `out/html/img/`, local build checks). **Do not hand-edit `out/` for game logic** — `npm run make-html` overwrites compiled output; frozen shell files are the exception (see `game-source-only.mdc`).
- Verify changes with a local build when behavior matters.
- `/robots.txt` (repo root) — ask crawlers not to index `source/`, `out/`, `scripts/`, `.cursor/` on GitHub.
- `source/robots.txt` — same policy for the playable build; copy to `out/html/robots.txt` when publishing.

## Image generation (addendum)

- **Code** — Only edit game logic and references under `source/` (e.g. `card-image: img/jacobs.webp` in `.scene.dry`).
- **Generated art** — Save new or updated images under `out/html/img/` (e.g. `out/html/img/jacobs.webp`). Do not put generated portraits or card art in `source/`.
- **Default format** — Card and advisor portraits: **240×300 WebP** (`quality` ~85). Resize or convert after generation if the source asset is larger or another format.
- **Aspect ratio** — Never stretch a source image to 240×300. Scale to **cover** the frame (preserve aspect ratio), then **center-crop** to 240×300; or letterbox if cropping would cut off the subject. Forcing `resize(240, 300)` on a landscape source will squash faces.
- Paths in scenes are relative to the playable build: `img/<name>.webp` → `out/html/img/<name>.webp` at runtime.
